  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section B — Baxter (TQ) solver: minimal reusable routine set (BaxterMatrix, TauEigensystem/Psi/τ, QSolve, Q1) ported from Experiments/Baxter_Solver_L2.wb. Only the load-bearing definitions are kept here; see that file for the full derivation, the spurious-vs-genuine motivation writeup (why a naive Baxter-matrix diagonalization overcounts states relative to the true weight-M subspace dimension dPred), and the validation/regression suite (stage-1 t2-eigenvalue checks and stage-2 end-to-end TQ-residual checks) that verified this pipeline. t2Coeffs below calls Section A's t2 directly (dedup: the shared companion-twist machinery lives only in Section A now).*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*a(u)=aFun is now an ALIAS for Section A's two-site ν1 (Yangian weight eigenvalue of T[1,1] on\n  the HWS) — same formula (u-θ1-hλ1)(u-θ2-hλ2), deduped so there is a single source of truth\n  instead of two copies that could drift. d(u)=Qθ(u), and τ0 = τ minus the J term (using\n  ee1=λ1+λ2-M, ee2=M). Qθ (=d) is defined LOCALLY here so this file is self-contained.\n  qpoly builds a polynomial from an ASCENDING coefficient list {c0,...,cM} (cM=1 for monic q_n);\n  formed in a dummy symbol first so substituting uu=0 gives the constant term rather than an\n  indeterminate 0^0.*)\nClearAll[aFun, τ0, Qθ, qpoly];\naFun[λ1_, λ2_][u_] := ν1[λ1, λ2][u];\nQθ[u_] := (u - θ1) (u - θ2);\nτ0[λ1_, λ2_, M_][u_] := (κ1 + κ2) u^2 - (θ1 + θ2) (κ1 + κ2) u - u h (κ1 (λ1 + λ2 - M) + κ2 M);\nqpoly[clist_, uu_] := Module[{x}, (clist . x^Range[0, Length[clist] - 1]) /. x -> uu];\n{aFun[1, 1][u], Qθ[u], τ0[1, 1, 1][u]}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
