"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.61em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-2.41em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-1.21em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-0.01em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:3.35em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"delimsizing mult\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:3.85em;\"><span style=\"top:-5.8499em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:9.2em;\"></span><span style=\"width:0.875em;height:7.200em;\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"0.875em\" height=\"7.200em\" viewBox=\"0 0 875 7200\"><path d=\"M76,0c-16.7,0,-25,3,-25,9c0,2,2,6.3,6,13c21.3,28.7,42.3,60.3,\n63,95c96.7,156.7,172.8,332.5,228.5,527.5c55.7,195,92.8,416.5,111.5,664.5\nc11.3,139.3,17,290.7,17,454c0,28,1.7,43,3.3,45l0,3609\nc-3,4,-3.3,16.7,-3.3,38c0,162,-5.7,313.7,-17,455c-18.7,248,-55.8,469.3,-111.5,664\nc-55.7,194.7,-131.8,370.3,-228.5,527c-20.7,34.7,-41.7,66.3,-63,95c-2,3.3,-4,7,-6,11\nc0,7.3,5.7,11,17,11c0,0,11,0,11,0c9.3,0,14.3,-0.3,15,-1c5.3,-5.3,10.3,-11,15,-17\nc242.7,-294.7,395.3,-681.7,458,-1161c21.3,-164.7,33.3,-350.7,36,-558\nl0,-3744c-2,-159.3,-10,-310.7,-24,-454c-53.3,-528,-210,-949.7,\n-470,-1265c-4.7,-6,-9.7,-11.7,-15,-17c-0.7,-0.7,-6.7,-1,-18,-1z\"/></svg></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:3.35em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">num states validated</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">41</span><span class=\"mclose\">∣</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mclose\">⟩</span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[237]= \\langle\\!\\lvert \\text{generator \\{a,b\\}}\\to \\left\\{2,1\\right\\},\\text{$\\varphi$(k)}\\to \\text{$\\alpha$ k},\\text{$\\alpha$ (universal value)}\\to -1.\\,+0.\\,\\,\\mathrm{i},\\text{normalization}\\to \\text{1-site FSoV determinant det1[f] = br1[f]/(f/.u->$\\theta$1); Section C's det[$\\lambda$1,$\\lambda$2][f] restricted to 1 site},\\text{max residual over rep sweep}\\to 0,\\text{reps validated}\\to \\begin{pmatrix}1 & 1\\\\2 & 1\\\\1 & 2\\\\2 & 2\\\\3 & 1\\\\1 & 3\\end{pmatrix},\\text{num states validated}\\to 41\\rvert\\!\\rangle",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "3400eb20-c3e2-4948-97c0-4327b1d374e0"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section G — Phase 1: the 2→1 site degeneration by pole cancellation.\nHypothesis (Paul): multiplying f by a polynomial P(u) with roots on site 2's inhomogeneity\ntower cancels site 2's contribution to the 2-site FSoV measure mu[λ1,λ2][1][u], collapsing\nthe site-1-restricted 2-site bracket br[λ1,λ2][1][P f] exactly onto the pure 1-site bracket\nbr1[λ1][f] (Section F), up to an explicit (λ1,λ2,θ)-dependent constant C. Derivation:\nmu[λ1,λ2][1][u] = Nn[λ1,λ2][1]/(Product_{k=0}^{λ1}(u-θ1-hk) Product_{k=0}^{λ2}(u-θ2-hk)) (1-Exp[2πi/h(u-θ2)]).\nTaking P(u) = Product_{k=0}^{λ2}(u-θ2-hk) cancels exactly the θ2-tower denominator factor.\nWhat remains is Nn[λ1,λ2][1](1-Exp[2πi/h(u-θ2)])/Product_{k=0}^{λ1}(u-θ1-hk); on the θ1-tower\nu=θ1+hk this oscillatory factor is a CONSTANT (independent of k), since u-θ2=θ1-θ2+hk and\nExp[2πi/h·hk]=Exp[2πi k]=1 for integer k, so the factor equals (1-Exp[2πi(θ1-θ2)/h])\nfor every lattice point in the θ1-tower. Hence mu[λ1,λ2][1]·P collapses to a fixed multiple of\nmu1[λ1] exactly (not just up to a leading-order approximation), giving the closed identity\nbr[λ1,λ2][1][P f] = C(λ1,λ2,θ)·br1[λ1][f] with C worked out below from Nn/nn/Nn1's closed forms.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*P1site2[λ2][u]: the site-2-tower-cancelling polynomial multiplying f before taking br[·][1][·].\n  C1pred[λ1,λ2]: the predicted constant, derived analytically from Nn[λ1,λ2][1]=nn[λ1,λ2][1]/(2πi(1-Exp[2πi(θ1-θ2)/h]))\n  and Nn1[λ1]=(-h)^λ1 λ1!/(2πi) (both closed forms already in the notebook/Section C,F): the oscillatory\n  factor's (1-Exp[...]) cancels against the same factor sitting inside Nn[·][1], leaving\n  C1pred = nn[λ1,λ2][1] / ((-h)^λ1 λ1!) = (-1)^(λ2-1) Product_{k=0}^{λ2}(θ2+kh-θ1).*)\nClearAll[P1site2,C1pred];\nP1site2[λ2_][u_] := Product[(u-θ2-h k),{k,0,λ2}];\nC1pred[λ1_,λ2_] := (-1)^(λ2-1) Product[(θ2+k h-θ1),{k,0,λ2}];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Test 1 — symbolic polynomial test functions f=u^j, j=0..λ1+2, across the full rep sweep.\n  Purely rational (no Exp), so Simplify should collapse the residual to a LITERAL 0.\n  This is the hard structural check on P1site2/C1pred with no numerical tolerance involved.*)\nClearAll[phase1PolyResid];\nphase1PolyResid = Flatten[Table[\n   Simplify[br[λ1,λ2][1][P1site2[λ2][u] u^j] - C1pred[λ1,λ2] br1[λ1][u^j]],\n   {rep,{{1,1},{2,1},{1,2},{2,2},{3,1},{1,3}}},\n   {λ1,{rep[[1]]}},{λ2,{rep[[2]]}},\n   {j,0,λ1+2}]];\nphase1PolyResid = DeleteDuplicates[Flatten[phase1PolyResid]];\nIf[phase1PolyResid =!= {0}, Abort[]];\n{\"Test 1 (symbolic monomials u^j) residuals\", phase1PolyResid}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"941591\" data-output-id=\"605\" data-out-n=\"245\" data-sub-idx=\"5\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"79\" data-sub-start=\"11\" data-sub-end=\"11\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[245]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrqj6hn3-jq124nh\" data-page-width-em=\"23\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRce1x0ZXh0e1Rlc3QgMSAoc3ltYm9saWMgbW9ub21pYWxzIHVcXnt9aikgcmVzaWR1YWxzfSxcbGVmdFx7MFxyaWdodFx9XHJpZ2h0XH0=\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">Test 1 (symbolic monomials u</span><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.25em;\"><span class=\"mord\">ˆ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\">j) residuals</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[245]= \\left\\{\\text{Test 1 (symbolic monomials u\\^{}j) residuals},\\left\\{0\\right\\}\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "cb69c5b8-9901-4af3-8d13-fb483211c0b8"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Test 2 — twisted monomials f = k^(u/h) u^j, symbolic k, across the full rep sweep.\n  Same structural check, now including the transcendental k^(u/h) factor that Q1 itself carries.*)\nClearAll[phase1TwistResid];\nphase1TwistResid = Flatten[Table[\n   Simplify[br[λ1,λ2][1][P1site2[λ2][u] k^(u/h) u^j] - C1pred[λ1,λ2] br1[λ1][k^(u/h) u^j]],\n   {rep,{{1,1},{2,1},{1,2},{2,2},{3,1},{1,3}}},\n   {λ1,{rep[[1]]}},{λ2,{rep[[2]]}},\n   {j,0,λ1+2}]];\nphase1TwistResid = DeleteDuplicates[Flatten[phase1TwistResid]];\nIf[phase1TwistResid =!= {0}, Abort[]];\n{\"Test 2 (twisted monomials k^(u/h) u^j) residuals\", phase1TwistResid}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"941591\" data-output-id=\"606\" data-out-n=\"250\" data-sub-idx=\"5\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"80\" data-sub-start=\"10\" data-sub-end=\"10\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[250]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrqj6ivk-knpsd6p\" data-page-width-em=\"23\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRce1x0ZXh0e1Rlc3QgMiAodHdpc3RlZCBtb25vbWlhbHMga1xee30odS9oKSB1XF57fWopIHJlc2lkdWFsc30sXGxlZnRcezBccmlnaHRcfVxyaWdodFx9\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">Test 2 (twisted monomials k</span><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.25em;\"><span class=\"mord\">ˆ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\">(u/h) u</span><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.25em;\"><span class=\"mord\">ˆ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\">j) residuals</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
