   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section I outcome — STEPS 0-2 CLOSED EXACTLY (genuine progress); STEP 3 OBSTRUCTED, reported\nprecisely per the stop condition rather than forced.\n\nSTEP 0 (baseline anchor) — CLOSED EXACTLY. det[λ1,λ2][k^(u/h)Q1] (Section C's full 2-site det, same\nk at both nodes) equals O[k,k] identically: worst residual 0 over the full 41-state, 6-rep sweep\n(Cell 108). This calibrates every convention used below and is the strongest new result of this\nsection — a genuine, exact bridge between the \"textbook\" 2-site FSoV scalar-product machinery and\nthe two-rotation overlap, on the diagonal k1=k2.\n\nSTEP 1 (covector identification) — CLOSED EXACTLY, clean closed form. ⟨x0[λ]|E21^m = γ_m(λ)·xL1[λ][{m}]\nidentically (pure representation theory, no θ/site dependence), with\n  γ_m(λ) = λ!/(λ-m)!  (falling factorial)\nverified exactly for λ=1,2,3, m=0..λ (Cells 109-110).\n\nSTEP 2 (slice factorization, the crux) — the naive conjecture x2[λ1,λ2][{s1,m}] ∝ xL1[λ1][{s1}]⊗xL1[λ2][{m}]\nis FALSE for m>=1 (only m=0 holds, Section E) — hard-Abort confirmed a genuine O(1) shape mismatch,\nnot a wrong constant (Cell 113). The TRUE structure, found and verified exactly (0 off-level nonzero\ncoefficients over 29 (λ1,λ2,s1,m) cases, Cell 117): x2[λ1,λ2][{s1,m}] decomposes EXACTLY within the\nFIXED-TOTAL-LEVEL subspace\n  x2[λ1,λ2][{s1,m}] = Σ_{s1'+m'=s1+m, 0<=s1'<=λ1, 0<=m'<=λ2} A[s1,m;s1',m'] xL1[λ1][{s1'}]⊗xL1[λ2][{m'}]\na genuine LEVEL-GRADED RECOUPLING (finer than the anticipated \"triangular in s1\" mixing — the total\nlevel L=s1+m, not s1 alone, is the conserved label), consistent with L=s1+s2 playing the role of the\nweight-sector M throughout this notebook. The coefficients A were NOT reduced to a closed form\n(would need solving what is effectively a CG-recoupling problem for this SoV basis) — flagged as the\nnatural next target for a future session, since it's clearly the right structural language.\n\nSTEP 3 (graded dictionary) — OBSTRUCTED. Five natural candidates were tried against the exactly-known\nO_m[k1] (extracted as (-1)^m m! · [k2^m] O2rot, exact since O2rot is a finite k2-polynomial by\nconstruction) on rep (2,1), state (1,0), m=0,1 (the cheapest gate, λ2=1):\n  1. Cm[m][k1] := br[λ1,λ2][1][Pm[m][u]k1^(u/h)Q1[u]] / (·|θ1), Pm[m][u]=Product[(u-θ2-hk),{k,0,m-1}]\n     (task's literal suggestion) — FAILS even at m=0 (Cm[0] has a genuinely different k1-SHAPE from\n     O_0[k1], not merely a wrong constant: Om-Cm is k1,k1^2-dependent, not proportional).\n  2. Unnormalized difference Bm[0]-Bm[1] vs O_0[k1] — FAILS with a fractional-power mismatch\n     (numerator carries a spurious k1^(1/3) prefactor Om lacks) — wrong structure entirely.\n  3. Normalized difference Cm[0]-Cm[1] vs O_0[k1] — FAILS: Cm[0]-Cm[1] has constant (k1^0) term\n     EXACTLY 0, but O_0[k1] has constant term 1 by construction — a hard mismatch at leading order.\n  4. Reversed-index hypothesis Cm[0]/O_{λ2}=O_1 (motivated by the fact that Phase-1's FULL insertion\n     Pm[λ2+1]=P1site2[λ2] maps to O_0, i.e. \"kill everything\" <-> bottom piece, suggesting a possible\n     m<->λ2-m reversal) — ratio Cm[0][k1]/O_1[k1] is NOT k1-independent (numerator/denominator have\n     different degree-2-in-k1 shapes) — FAILS.\n  5. Top-level Cm[λ2][k1] (kill all but the top level) vs O_{λ2}[k1] directly — also NOT proportional\n     (both degree-2 in k1, but not scalar multiples) — FAILS.\nNone of the five closes even at this single cheapest (m=0 or m=1, one state) gate, so per the stop\ncondition (\"report the exact ratio... as a function of state labels — do not force it\") this is\nreported as an OBSTRUCTION rather than pursued to the full sweep. ROOT CAUSE (best diagnosis):\nPm[m][u] reshapes the WEIGHT of the tower-1-ONLY residue sum br[λ1,λ2][1][·] (which never evaluates\nat any tower-2 point) — it does not literally \"select\" a θ2-level in any sense connected to the\nlevel-m generator power E21^m; STEP 2 showed the genuine site-2 grading lives in a basis-recoupling\nstructure (A[s1,m;s1',m']), not in a value of u, so a construction built purely from evaluating f at\nθ1 was never structurally positioned to see the m-grading correctly — the correct STEP-3 object, if\nit exists, likely needs to import the STEP-2 recoupling coefficients explicitly (e.g. as an extra\nsum over s1' with A-weights) rather than a single bracket evaluation, which was not attempted here\ngiven the A[s1,m;s1',m'] closed form itself remains unsolved.\n\nEverything hard-verified: STEP 0 (41 states, residual 0), STEP 1 (9 (λ,m) cases, exact), STEP 2's\nlevel-conservation (29 cases, exact 0 off-level coefficients). STEP 3/4 not closed — reported here as\nthe precise failure point (which step: 3; what structure: single-bracket candidates cannot see the\nSTEP-2 level-recoupling) rather than assembled into a forced, wrong formula.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section J — closed form of the recoupling matrix A[s1,m;s1',m'] and full assembly.\nStrategy: build STANDALONE symbolic-θ versions of the SoV machinery (t1Sym/t2Sym/xL1Sym/x2Sym,\ntaking θ1,θ2 as EXPLICIT function arguments instead of reading the notebook's global numeric θ1,θ2)\nso the linear system for A can be solved as exact rational functions of θ1,θ2,h — this avoids the\nmemoization gotcha (xL1/x2's memoized cache is keyed only on (λ,s), not on the global θ's, so\nBlock-ing θ1,θ2 to symbols would silently return STALE numeric cached values, not recompute\nsymbolically). G, χ2 (companion-twist data) stay the existing fixed numerics — they don't depend on\nθ. Validated against the live numeric xL1/x2 by substitution before use.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Standalone single-site symbolic-θ fused hierarchy (mirrors Section E's t1/qdet1/xL1, θ1->θa).\n  (*why θa,θb as function ARGUMENTS, not literally θ1,θ2*) θ1,θ2 are GLOBAL symbols already assigned\n  numeric values (1/3, 1/7) in Cell 1 — calling xL1Sym[θ1][...] would silently substitute those\n  numbers immediately, NOT stay symbolic. The functions below take θa (site 1) / θa,θb (two-site) as\n  ordinary pattern arguments so callers can pass either the free symbols θA,θB (genuinely unassigned,\n  for symbolic exploration) or the numeric θ1,θ2 (for validation against the live machinery).\n  (*why GSym not G*) G's (1,1) entry χ1=κ1+κ2 is a ~30-digit-precision APPROXIMATE real number\n  (κ1=Exp[IZeta[3]] is transcendental) — mixing that into Simplify with exact symbolic θA,θB leaves\n  ugly unsimplified 10^-28-type precision residues instead of collapsing cleanly. GSym uses a fresh\n  free symbol χ1sym in G's place so everything stays exact; verified below whether χ1sym survives in\n  the final A-coefficients (expected: cancels, matching Section E/F's χ-independent normalized SoV\n  covector ratios).*)\nClearAll[GSym,t1Sym,qdet1Sym,ν1SingleSym,xL1Sym];\nGSym = {{χ1sym,-1},{1,0}};\nt1Sym[θa_][λ_][0,s_][u_] := IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ,0}]];\nt1Sym[θa_][λ_][a_,0][u_] := IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ,0}]];\nt1Sym[θa_][λ_][1,1][u_] := Sum[L[λ][i,j][u-θa] GSym[[j,i]],{i,2},{j,2}];\nqdet1Sym[θa_][λ_][u_] := L[λ][1,1][u-θa].L[λ][2,2][u-θa-h] - L[λ][2,1][u-θa].L[λ][1,2][u-θa-h];\nt1Sym[θa_][λ_][2,1][u_] := qdet1Sym[θa][λ][u];  (*χ2=1 exactly, no need for a symbolic stand-in*)\nt1Sym[θa_][λ_][1,s_/;s>1][u_] := t1Sym[θa][λ][1,s-1][u].t1Sym[θa][λ][1,1][u+(s-1)h] - t1Sym[θa][λ][2,1][u+(s-1)h].t1Sym[θa][λ][1,s-2][u];\nν1SingleSym[θa_][λ_][u_] := (u-θa-h λ);\nxL1Sym[θa_][λ_][{0}] := xSingle[λ][{0}];\nxL1Sym[θa_][λ_][{s_}] := xSingle[λ][{0}].t1Sym[θa][λ][1,s][θa] / Product[ν1SingleSym[θa][λ][θa+(p-1)h],{p,1,s}];\n\n(*Standalone two-site symbolic-θ hierarchy (mirrors Section A's L1/L2/T/t2/ν1/x2, θ1,θ2->θa,θb).*)\nClearAll[L1Sym,L2Sym,TSym,t2Sym,qdetTSym,ν1TwoSym,x2Sym];\nL1Sym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][i_,j_][u_] := KroneckerProduct[L[λ1][i,j][u-θa],IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ2,0}]]];\nL2Sym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][i_,j_][u_] := KroneckerProduct[IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ1,0}]],L[λ2][i,j][u-θb]];\nTSym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][i_,j_][u_] := Sum[L1Sym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][i,k][u].L2Sym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][k,j][u],{k,2}];\nt2Sym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][0,s_][u_] := IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ1,0}]dim[{λ2,0}]];\nt2Sym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][a_,0][u_] := IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ1,0}]dim[{λ2,0}]];\nt2Sym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][1,1][u_] := Sum[TSym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][i,j][u] GSym[[j,i]],{i,2},{j,2}];\nqdetTSym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][u_] := TSym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][1,1][u].TSym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][2,2][u-h] - TSym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][2,1][u].TSym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][1,2][u-h];\nt2Sym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][2,1][u_] := qdetTSym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][u];\nt2Sym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][1,s_/;s>1][u_] := t2Sym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][1,s-1][u].t2Sym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][1,1][u+(s-1)h] - t2Sym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][2,1][u+(s-1)h].t2Sym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][1,s-2][u];\nν1TwoSym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][u_] := (u-θa-h λ1)(u-θb-h λ2);\nx2Sym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][{0,0}] := KroneckerProduct[xSingle[λ1][{0}],xSingle[λ2][{0}]];\nx2Sym[θa_,θb_][λ1_,λ2_][{s1_,s2_}] := x2Sym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][{0,0}].t2Sym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][1,s1][θa].t2Sym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][1,s2][θb] /\n  (Product[ν1TwoSym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][θa+(k-1)h],{k,1,s1}] Product[ν1TwoSym[θa,θb][λ1,λ2][θb+(k-1)h],{k,1,s2}]);",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Validation: symbolic constructions (called with θA,θB,χ1sym, then substituted to the actual\n  numeric θ1,θ2,χ1) must reproduce the live numeric xL1/x2 exactly — a port-fidelity check before\n  trusting the symbolic run.*)\nvalXL1 = Table[\n  Chop[N[(Flatten[xL1Sym[θA][λ][{s}]]/.{θA->θ1,χ1sym->χ1}) - Flatten[xL1[λ][{s}]]],10^-10]\n,{λ,{1,2,3}},{s,0,λ}];\nvalX2 = Table[\n  Chop[N[(Flatten[x2Sym[θA,θB][λ1,λ2][{s1,s2}]]/.{θA->θ1,θB->θ2,χ1sym->χ1}) - Flatten[x2[λ1,λ2][{s1,s2}]]],10^-10]\n,{λ1,{1,2}},{λ2,{1,2}},{s1,0,λ1},{s2,0,λ2}];\nworstValXL1 = Max[Abs[Flatten[valXL1]]];\nworstValX2 = Max[Abs[Flatten[valX2]]];\nIf[worstValXL1 > 10^-8 || worstValX2 > 10^-8, Abort[]];\n{\"Symbolic-θ,χ1 port-fidelity: xL1Sym vs xL1\", worstValXL1, \"x2Sym vs x2\", worstValX2}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"941591\" data-output-id=\"640\" data-out-n=\"446\" data-sub-idx=\"6\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"125\" data-sub-start=\"12\" data-sub-end=\"12\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[446]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrqj78ei-nne89fb\" data-page-width-em=\"23\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRce1x0ZXh0e1N5bWJvbGljLSRcdGhldGEkLCRcY2hpJDEgcG9ydC1maWRlbGl0eTogeEwxU3ltIHZzIHhMMX0sMCxcdGV4dHt4MlN5bSB2cyB4Mn0sMFxyaWdodFx9\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">Symbolic-</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mord\">,</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">χ</span><span class=\"mord\">1 port-fidelity: xL1Sym vs xL1</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">x2Sym vs x2</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
