  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section J final report — genuine partial closed form found; sum rule and full assembly did NOT\nclose within the time budget; reported precisely rather than forced.\n\nWHAT WAS FOUND (hard-verified, symbolic, exact):\n\n1. DIAGONAL closed form. Working with GENUINELY free symbols θA,θB (h=1, χ1 also symbolized as\n   χ1sym to avoid ~30-digit numeric-precision contamination of Simplify — a real gotcha, see Cells\n   125-126) and standalone symbolic-θ ports of the entire t1/t2/xL1/x2 machinery (port-fidelity\n   checked to 0 against the live numeric objects first), the DIAGONAL of the recoupling matrix is:\n     A[s1,m;s1,m] = FallingFactorial[s1+θ12, m] / FallingFactorial[λ1+θ12, m],  θ12 := θ1-θ2\n   equivalently Pochhammer[s1+θ12-m+1,m]/Pochhammer[λ1+θ12-m+1,m]. Verified exactly (Factor'd to\n   confirm) against every diagonal entry for λ1,λ2∈{1,2,3} (16 cases, Cell 131). At s1=λ1 this gives\n   A[λ1,m;λ1,m]=1 for all m — the extremal-s1 boundary is always unmixed, consistent with Section\n   I's earlier numeric finding.\n\n2. TRIANGULARITY (structural characterization, Step 5's fallback, hard-verified): each fixed-level-L\n   block of A (rows/columns indexed by s1'∈[max(0,L-λ2),min(L,λ1)]) is upper-triangular in s1\n   ascending order — x2[λ1,λ2][{s1,m}] only involves xL1[λ1][{s1'}]⊗xL1[λ2][{m'}] with s1'>=s1\n   (Cell 132, confirmed for the λ1=λ2=3, L=2 block; consistent with every other case inspected). Its\n   inverse is therefore also triangular and was computed exactly for that block (Cell 133) — the\n   inverse's diagonal is the reciprocal 1/A[s1,m;s1,m] as expected for a triangular matrix, but its\n   off-diagonal entries did not reduce to a form as clean as A's own diagonal.\n\n3. RAW (unnormalized) numerator B := A rescaled by the known D1/D2 normalization ratios (per hint 5)\n   is POLYNOMIAL rather than rational (Cells 129-130) — genuinely simpler in that sense (no\n   denominators to track) but its own closed form was not fully cracked either; its diagonal\n   reproduces Section E's already-known μSite2[λ2,s1]=Product[(θ12+k-1-λ2),{k,1,s1}] at m=0 exactly,\n   a useful cross-check but the general (s1,m) entries remain empirical data only.\n\nWHAT DID NOT CLOSE:\n\n- General OFF-diagonal closed form for A (or B): despite the clean diagonal, the off-diagonal\n  entries (Cell 131's full sweep, 127 symbolic entries for λ1,λ2<=3) resisted pattern-matching by\n  hand within the time budget — they are genuine rational functions of θ12 of growing complexity\n  with level L, plausibly a Hahn/Racah-polynomial-type structure (the natural discrete-orthogonal-\n  polynomial family for this kind of two-site recoupling problem) rather than a simple product form.\n\n- SUM RULE (Step 2's request): a natural-looking conjecture,\n    Σ_{s1'+m'=s1+m} Binomial[λ1,s1']Binomial[λ2,m'] A[s1,m;s1',m'] = Binomial[λ1,s1]Binomial[λ2,m],\n  was spotted from a SINGLE hand-checked data point (λ1=λ2=3, level L=1) and found, on systematic\n  testing (Cell 136), to be a coincidence of that specific case (λ1=λ2, L=1) — it fails for λ1!=λ2\n  even at L=1, and fails for λ1=λ2 at L>=2 too (29 of 81 tested cases). No corrected sum rule was\n  found in the remaining time. This is reported as a genuine negative result, not a working\n  consistency check.\n\n- ASSEMBLY (Steps 3-4): building on Section I's already-extensive (5 failed candidates) attempts,\n  two MORE candidates were tried using the new diagonal/triangularity insight: (i) a linear\n  combination Cm[m][k1] = Σ_m' w_{m,m'} O_m'[k1] (motivated by triangularity) — Solve found NO\n  consistent weights even for the simplest 2-unknown case (rep (2,1), m=0; Cell 134, `Solve::ivar`\n  debugging revealed and fixed an unrelated variable-name collision with a pre-existing global `w0`,\n  but the corrected computation still gives an INCONSISTENT overdetermined system, `Solve[...]={}`);\n  (ii) the standard-SoV-theory guess that x2[{s1,s2}].Psi factorizes as a simple product\n  Q1(θ1+s1h)Q1(θ2+s2h) (which would let A's inverse convert graded pieces directly into Q1 VALUES,\n  bypassing the Section-I bracket recipes entirely) — tested numerically (Cell 135) and found FALSE\n  (spread ≈4.04, not 0, across the 6 states of rep (2,1) at several (s1,s2)). The genuine SoV\n  reconstruction relating x2.Psi to Q1 is evidently NOT a bare product — consistent with why\n  Section C's `det` needed the full 2×2 Wronskian-type {f,uf} determinant structure rather than a\n  naive product to encode the L=2 scalar product; the analogous object for x2.Psi individually is\n  apparently richer still and was not identified.\n\nBOTTOM LINE: the recoupling matrix A has a genuine, clean, fully verified DIAGONAL closed form and a\nverified TRIANGULAR structure — real, useful, novel results. The full off-diagonal closed form, a\nworking sum rule, and the Steps-3/4 assembly of O[k1,k2] via A-weighted bracket objects were all\nattempted systematically (8 total candidate constructions across Sections I and J) and none closed.\nThis is reported as the precise state of the obstruction rather than forced into an incorrect\nformula. Natural next steps for a future session: (a) recognize/derive the off-diagonal pattern via\nthe Hirota recursion directly (a genuine 3-term recursion in m, not attempted here) rather than\npattern-matching the closed-form solution; (b) find the correct (necessarily more structured than a\nbare product) formula for x2[{s1,s2}].Psi in terms of Q1, which is the actual missing bridge for\nSteps 3-4, independent of A's closed form.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*BOXED RESULT — the one fully closed, hard-asserted formula from Section J:\n     A[s1,m;s1,m] = FallingFactorial[s1+θ12,m] / FallingFactorial[λ1+θ12,m],   θ12 = θ1-θ2, h=1.\n   Re-verified here numerically at the notebook's ACTUAL θ1=1/3,θ2=1/7 (not just symbolically),\n   directly against the live decompX2 diagonal entries, λ1,λ2∈{1,2,3} sweep — hard-asserted.\n   (*why Pochhammer not FallingFactorial*) FallingFactorial[x,0] does NOT auto-simplify to 1 in this\n   kernel for ANY x, even plain integers (a genuine quirk — Pochhammer[x+1,0] DOES reduce to 1\n   correctly) — using Pochhammer[x-n+1,n] (algebraically identical to FallingFactorial[x,n]) avoids\n   silently carrying an unevaluated symbolic husk through Chop/N/Max.*)\nClearAll[Adiag];\nAdiag[λ1_,s1_,m_] := Pochhammer[(s1+θ1-θ2)-m+1,m]/Pochhammer[(λ1+θ1-θ2)-m+1,m];\ndiagFinalCheck = {};\nDo[\n  Do[\n    Do[\n      Module[{d,assoc,val},\n        d = decompX2[λ1,λ2][s1,m];\n        assoc = Association[d];\n        val = If[KeyExistsQ[assoc,{s1,m}], assoc[{s1,m}], 0];\n        AppendTo[diagFinalCheck, {λ1,λ2,s1,m, Chop[N[val]-N[Adiag[λ1,s1,m]],10^-9]}]\n      ]\n    ,{m,0,λ2}]\n  ,{s1,0,λ1}]\n,{λ1,{1,2,3}},{λ2,{1,2,3}}];\nworstDiagFinal = Max[Abs[diagFinalCheck[[All,5]]]];\nIf[worstDiagFinal > 10^-8, Abort[]];\n{\"BOXED: A[s1,m;s1,m] = Pochhammer[s1+θ1-θ2-m+1,m]/Pochhammer[λ1+θ1-θ2-m+1,m] — verified at the live numeric θ1,θ2\",\n \"worst deviation\", worstDiagFinal, \"num (λ1,λ2,s1,m) cases\", Length[diagFinalCheck]}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"941591\" data-output-id=\"651\" data-out-n=\"496\" data-sub-idx=\"7\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"137\" data-sub-start=\"25\" data-sub-end=\"26\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[496]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrqj7g2r-mvitsyo\" data-page-width-em=\"23\" data-latex-b64=\"\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">BOXED: A[s1,m;s1,m] = Pochhammer[s1+</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mord\">1-</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mord\">2-m+1,m]/Pochhammer[</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">λ</span><span class=\"mord\">1+</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mord\">1-</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mord\">2-m+1,m] — verified at the live numeric </span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mord\">1,</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">worst deviation</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">num (</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">λ</span><span class=\"mord\">1,</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">λ</span><span class=\"mord\">2,s1,m) cases</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">81</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
